        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36a.17"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">17</fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <hi rend="caps">TELEPHONE 342-6919, A.C.</hi> 913
                    
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>A Holiday Inn Sign</figDesc>
                        <p>Holiday Inn
                        THE WORLDS INNKEEPER
                        REG. U. S. PAT. OFF.</p>
                    </figure> 
                    Holiday Inn&#174; <hi rend="caps">OF KANSAS CITY 
                        <lb/>
                    (DOWNTOWN TOWERS)
                        <lb/>
                    424 MINNESOTA AVENUE 
                        <lb/>
                    KANSAS CITY, KANSAS</hi> 66101
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>June 23, 1972</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>It was indeed a great pleasure for me. to have met you yesterday. You may rest assured that I will do all I can to sell your book. A book is like poetry &#8212; once it is written it takes its own cause and for those there are to hear it &#8212; the voice is heard in its dream and its reality.</p> 
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <figure><figDesc>A man in 18th Century clothing holding a lantern and gesturing to his left</figDesc></figure> <figure><figDesc>A man and woman with suitcases and golf bag standing outside a car</figDesc></figure> <figure><figDesc>A man, woman, boy, and girl seated at a table, eating</figDesc></figure> <figure><figDesc>A woman by a swimming pool, a man seated at an umbrella-covered table</figDesc></figure> <figure><figDesc>Eight men, seven of whom are seated around a table, at a meeting</figDesc></figure> 
                    REG U S. PAT. OFF                   HOLIDAY PRESS 
                </fw>                               
                
                <fw>2</fw> 
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36a.18"/>
               
                <fw type="curatorial">18</fw>
                    
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <hi rend="caps">TELEPHONE 342-6919, A.C.</hi> 913
                    
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>A Holiday Inn Sign</figDesc>
                        <p>Holiday Inn
                        THE WORLDS INNKEEPER
                        REG. U. S. PAT. OFF.</p>
                    </figure> 
                    Holiday Inn&#174; <hi rend="caps">OF KANSAS CITY
                        <lb/>
                    (DOWNTOWN TOWERS)
                        <lb/>
                    424 MINNESOTA AVENUE 
                        <lb/>
                    KANSAS CITY, KANSAS</hi> 66101
                </fw>
                
                <p>Mrs. Young called me and said that you wanted to have the poem which I mentioned in our talk. This poem was published in a magazine entitled "The Little Flower" and it is the only poem which I have written that has been published. The poem is called "Sleep In Joy."</p> 
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <figure><figDesc>A man in 18th Century clothing holding a lantern and gesturing to his left</figDesc></figure> <figure><figDesc>A man and woman with suitcases and golf bag standing outside a car</figDesc></figure> <figure><figDesc>A man, woman, boy, and girl seated at a table, eating</figDesc></figure> <figure><figDesc>A woman by a swimming pool, a man seated at an umbrella-covered table</figDesc></figure> <figure><figDesc>Eight men, seven of whom are seated around a table, at a meeting</figDesc></figure> 
                    REG U S. PAT. OFF                   HOLIDAY PRESS 
                </fw>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36a.19"/>
                    
                <fw type="curatorial">19</fw>
                    
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <hi rend="caps">TELEPHONE 342-6919, A.C.</hi> 913
                        
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>A Holiday Inn Sign</figDesc>
                        <p>Holiday Inn
                        THE WORLDS INNKEEPER
                        REG. U. S. PAT. OFF.</p>
                    </figure>
                    Holiday Inn&#174; <hi rend="caps">OF KANSAS CITY 
                        <lb/>
                    (DOWNTOWN TOWERS)
                        <lb/>
                    424 MINNESOTA AVENUE 
                        <lb/>
                    KANSAS CITY, KANSAS</hi> 66101
                </fw>
                
                <lg>
                    <l>Dream dreams of other lives</l>
                    <l>down through the ages of myth.</l>
                    <l>Recreating for us to see</l>
                    <l>that part of God's eternity.</l>
                </lg>
                
                <p>I am honored that you liked it and after I left you and was sitting in my room I wrote another which I trust you might enjoy.</p>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <figure><figDesc>A man in 18th Century clothing holding a lantern and gesturing to his left</figDesc></figure> <figure><figDesc>A man and woman with suitcases and golf bag standing outside a car</figDesc></figure> <figure><figDesc>A man, woman, boy, and girl seated at a table, eating</figDesc></figure> <figure><figDesc>A woman by a swimming pool, a man seated at an umbrella-covered table</figDesc></figure> <figure><figDesc>Eight men, seven of whom are seated around a table, at a meeting</figDesc></figure> 
                    REG U S. PAT. OFF                   HOLIDAY PRESS 
                </fw>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36a.20"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">20</fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <hi rend="caps">TELEPHONE 342-6919, A.C.</hi> 913
                    
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>A Holiday Inn Sign</figDesc>
                        <p>Holiday Inn
                        THE WORLDS INNKEEPER
                        REG. U. S. PAT. OFF.</p>
                    </figure> 
                    Holiday Inn&#174; <hi rend="caps">OF KANSAS CITY 
                        <lb/>
                    (DOWNTOWN TOWERS)
                        <lb/>
                    424 MINNESOTA AVENUE 
                        <lb/>
                    KANSAS CITY, KANSAS</hi> 66101
                </fw>
                
                <lg>
                    <l>"Upon Meeting John Neihardt"</l>
                </lg>
                <lg>
                    <l><hi rend="caps">IT WAS AS IF LIVING LEGEND COME TO LIFE,</hi></l>
                    <l><hi rend="caps">SHORT OF STATURE, TALL OF LIFE &#8212;</hi></l>
                    <l><hi rend="caps">TELLING TALES OF YOUTH, REMEMBERED,</hi></l>
                    <l><hi rend="caps">NOW THE MEAT FOR OLDER MEN.</hi></l>
                    <l><hi rend="caps">JOHN, JOHN, GO ON AND ON</hi></l>
                    <l><hi rend="caps">THY WILL IS STRONG &#8212;</hi></l>
                    <l><hi rend="caps">AND WE WILL MEET AGAIN &#8212;</hi></l>
                    <l><hi rend="caps">WHERE THE CIRCLE IS.</hi></l> 
                </lg>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <figure><figDesc>A man in 18th Century clothing holding a lantern and gesturing to his left</figDesc></figure> <figure><figDesc>A man and woman with suitcases and golf bag standing outside a car</figDesc></figure> <figure><figDesc>A man, woman, boy, and girl seated at a table, eating</figDesc></figure> <figure><figDesc>A woman by a swimming pool, a man seated at an umbrella-covered table</figDesc></figure> <figure><figDesc>Eight men, seven of whom are seated around a table, at a meeting</figDesc></figure> 
                    REG U S. PAT. OFF                   HOLIDAY PRESS
                </fw>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36a.21"/>
                    
                <fw type="curatorial">21</fw>     
                    
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <hi rend="caps">TELEPHONE 342-6919, A.C.</hi> 913
                    
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>A Holiday Inn Sign</figDesc>
                        <p>Holiday Inn
                        THE WORLDS INNKEEPER
                        REG. U. S. PAT. OFF.</p>
                    </figure> 
                    Holiday Inn&#174; <hi rend="caps">OF KANSAS CITY 
                        <lb/>
                    (DOWNTOWN TOWERS)
                        <lb/>
                    424 MINNESOTA AVENUE 
                        <lb/>
                    KANSAS CITY, KANSAS</hi> 66101
                </fw>
                
                <p>Again my thanks and I will convey your wishes to Miss Frost and I will look forward to seeing you again in October</p>
                    
                    <salute><del>W</del> With all best wishes,</salute>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Paul Dimmitt</signed>
                
